build/
dist/
*.spec

# Vendor MSIs (LogMeIn, etc.) — kept locally for build.ps1 -LogmeinMsi but
# never tracked. Each MSP has their own copy; bytes don't belong in the repo.
vendor/
*.msi

# NOTE: We used to ignore watchtower.ico + the two wizard BMPs, but the
# GitHub Actions Windows runner doesn't have libcairo-2.dll installed
# (cairosvg's Python bindings work but the underlying native lib is
# missing), so the workflow couldn't regenerate them on demand and
# every published installer shipped with the generic Inno chrome.
#
# Now these files are TRACKED in git so the workflow uses the pre-
# rendered copies committed from a dev box where cairosvg fully works.
# build.ps1 still calls make_*.py for local builds where they're
# missing, but those scripts won't run in CI because the files are
# already there.
#
# To refresh: edit favicon.svg / wizard-banner.svg locally, then
# `python make_wizard_images.py && python make_icon.py` and commit
# the updated BMPs/ICO alongside the SVG change.
